mmc: dw_mmc: honor 1-bit bus-width from the device tree

dwmci_setup_cfg() advertises MMC_MODE_4BIT whenever the host is not
8-bit capable, so "bus-width = <1>" in the DT is silently promoted to
4-bit. On Luckfox Nova (RK3308B) the first CMD6 data read after
switching the bus to 4-bit fails with a Start Bit Error and wedges the
controller, while every 1-bit transfer works; honoring the DT bus-width
makes the SD card usable. (Linux orders the SD init the other way
around - CMD6 high-speed switch first, in 1-bit, then ACMD6 - which is
why the same slot works at 4 bits there.)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/dw_mmc.c b/drivers/mmc/dw_mmc.c
index 89a8113..2ac84a2 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/dw_mmc.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/dw_mmc.c
@@ -763,9 +763,11 @@ void dwmci_setup_cfg(struct mmc_config *cfg, struct dwmci_host *host,
 	if (host->buswidth == 8) {
 		cfg->host_caps |= MMC_MODE_8BIT;
 		cfg->host_caps &= ~MMC_MODE_4BIT;
-	} else {
+	} else if (host->buswidth == 4) {
 		cfg->host_caps |= MMC_MODE_4BIT;
 		cfg->host_caps &= ~MMC_MODE_8BIT;
+	} else {
+		cfg->host_caps &= ~(MMC_MODE_8BIT | MMC_MODE_4BIT);
 	}
 	cfg->host_caps |= MMC_MODE_HS | MMC_MODE_HS_52MHz;
 
